  "name": "JCVI-Syn3.0 (minimal cell)",
  "niche": {
    "entity_count": 60,
    "description": "Curated minimal-essential roster \u00d7 CDS GCF_000027325.1 ASM2732v1 (M. genitalium G37 \u2014 Syn3.0 minimal-cell template) (NCBI, public domain). 16 loci: the translation/transcription/replication core (EF-Tu/EF-G, RNA pol, DNA pol III, ribosomal proteins, DnaK/GroEL) + the glycolysis ATP core (Syn3.0 has no TCA) + a one-carbon/amino-acid exchange anchor (glyA). JCVI-Syn3.0: a DESIGNED minimal cell, 531,560 bp / 473 genes (149 of unknown function) [Hutchison/Gibson 2016, Science aad6253]. PROVENANCE: no wild Syn3.0 assembly exists \u2014 baked from the M. genitalium G37 minimal-cell template (the Syn3.0 minimization lineage). Modeled as an obligate symbiont with the RICH DEFINED MEDIUM as the host abstraction (it grows ONLY in rich medium). The host-coupling kernel reads role + the SymbiosisCapacity lever (ADR-019 S5, Mode B).",
    "temp_optimum": 0.62,
    "parent_key": null,
    "trophic_role": "symbiont",
    "host_key": "default"
  },
